..TEXT:
In the great battle of Monte Aperto.  The river
Arbia is a few miles south of Siena.  The traveller crosses it on
his way to Rome.  In this battle the banished Ghibellines of
Florence, joining the Sienese, gained a victory over the Guelfs,
and retook the city of Florence.  Before the battle Buonaguida,
Syndic of Siena, presented the keys of the city to the Virgin
Mary in the Cathedral, and made a gift to her of the city and the
neighboring country.  After the battle the standard of the
vanquished Florentines, together with their battle-bell, the
Martinella, was tied to the tail of a jackass and dragged in the
dirt.  See Amp@ere, ^Voyage Dantesque~, 254.
..TCHR:
651
..AUTH:
